y":"service tool T3880422"}]},{"node":"text","body":"."}]},{"node":"text","body":" \r\n"},{"node":"instruction","body":[{"node":"text","body":"Refit the spark plugs (see "},{"node":"link","body":[{"node":"text","body":"Spark Plugs - Renew"}],"target-id":"81064799207544459-2","target-base-id":"5914875531"},{"node":"text","body":")."}]}]}]},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"}],"metadata":{"ModelsTaxonomyLink":"PJZ; PJ1; PB1","MarketsTaxonomyLink":"All"},"type":"TextModule"},{"node":"textmodule","body":[{"node":"title","body":[{"node":"text","body":"Perform the following operations"}]},{"node":"text","body":"\r\n"},{"node":"p","body":[{"node":"text","body":"Perform the following operations:"}]},{"node":"text","body":"\r\n"}],"metadata":{"Publication":"SM","MarketsTaxonomyLink":"All"},"type":"TextModule"},{"node":"textmodule","body":[{"node":"title","body":[{"node":"text","body":"Camshaft install operations PB1 PJ1 PJZ"}]},{"node":"text","body":"\r\n"},{"node":"ul","body":[{"node":"li","body":[{"node":"p","body":[{"node":"link","body":[{"node":"text","body":"Camshaft Drive Chain Tensioner - Installation"}],"target-id":"27021603662387467-2","target-base-id":"5898164491"}]}]},{"node":"text","body":" \r\n"},{"node":"li","body":[{"node":"p","body":[{"node":"link","body":[{"node":"text","body":"Crankshaft End Cover - Installation"}],"target-id":"54043201339078795-2","target-base-id":"5810632843"}]}]},{"node":"text","body":" \r\n"},{"node":"li","body":[{"node":"p","body":[{"node":"link","body":[{"node":"text","body":"Camshaft Cover - Installation"}],"target-id":"27021603578414859-2","target-base-id":"5814191883"}]}]},{"node":"text","body":" "}],"type":"disc"}],"metadata":{"ModelsTaxonomyLink":"PJZ; PJ1; PB1","MarketsTaxonomyLink":"All"},"type":"TextModule"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"}],"ancestors":["1342193291"],"parent":"1342193291","lastUpdate":"2024-03-11T08:19:32.000Z","metadata":{"markets":["All"],"_id":"661d30bf252ffca2459277fe"},"search":["Camshafts - Installation","Make sure the motorcycle is stabilised and adequately supported.","Do not support the motorcycle on any ancillary component, the exhaust system or any other non structural parts of the motorcycle frame.","A correctly supported motorcycle will help prevent it from falling.","An unstable motorcycle may fall resulting in motorcycle damage, serious injury or death.","Accurate camshaft timing can only be obtained using the correct timing method and service tools as described below.","The camshaft sprockets are attached to the camshafts using slotted bolt holes. This allows for very accurate valve timing and therefore improved performance and fuel economy. Never fit the camshaft sprockets without correctly setting the camshaft timing using the service tools and timing procedure described below. Severe engine damage will result from incorrect valve timing adjustment.","If removed, refit the sprockets to their camshafts with the original fixings. Do not fully tighten at this stage.","If not already installed, Insert ","service tool T3880422"," into the timing hole in the crankcase.","Turn the engine clockwise until the pin can be inserted fully into the crankshaft.","T3880422 - Crankshaft Timing Pin","Timing hole in crankcase","If removed, refit the camshaft caps dowels as noted for removal.","Camshaft cap dowels","Thoroughly clean the camshafts and journals. Lubricate the camshafts with clean engine oil before fitting to the cylinder head.","Locate each camshaft to the cylinder head and make sure the camshafts are correctly identified (see ","Camshaft - Identification",") and are also correctly located over their respective valve banks.","With the camshaft alignment mark pointing inwards, fit the camshaft drive chain over the exhaust sprocket.","Make sure there is no slack between the crankshaft and exhaust sprocket when the sprocket bolts are centrally located within the slotted holes. Make sure alignment marks on the end of the camshaft journals are pointing inwards.","With the camshaft alignment mark pointing inwards, fit the camshaft drive chain over the inlet sprocket.","Make sure the bolts on the inlet sprocket are also centrally located within the slotted holes when there is no slack between the exhaust and inlet sprockets.","Check that the camshaft drive chain is correctly located around the crankshaft and both camshaft sprockets.","Check the alignment marks on the front end of the camshaft journals are pointing inwards.","Alignment marks","Fit service tool ","service tool T3880421"," into the camshaft timing slots.","T3880421 - Camshaft Timing Plate","Camshaft slots","Lubricate the camshaft bearing areas of the camshaft caps with clean engine oil. Fit the camshaft caps and camshaft drive chain top pad.","Tighten the camshaft caps fixings in the following two stages:","Stage 1","Tighten the fixings in the sequence shown to ","5 Nm",".","Camshaft Caps Tightening Sequence","Stage 2","Tighten the fixings in the sequence shown to ","12 Nm",".","Camshaft Caps Tightening Sequence","If any components have been renewed, the valve clearances must be checked and adjusted. Running with incorrectly adjusted valve clearances may cause excess engine noise, rough running and engine damage.","Check that the camshaft drive chain is engaged around the camshaft drive sprocket on the crankshaft, the camshaft sprockets and the camshaft drive chain is positioned against the tensioner blade.","Fit the ","service tool T3880419"," and tighten the fixings to ","10 Nm",".","T3880419 - Camshaft Timing Tensioner","Fixings","The torque value stated is very important to accurate timing. Always use the correct value of 0.6 Nm as set using the ","T3880609 - Timing Torque Limiter",". Using an incorrect torque value will result in incorrect valve timing being set, or damage to the tensioner blade or other valve train components. Either condition may result in serious damage to the engine, reduced engine performance, or reduced fuel economy.","Using ","service tool T3880609",", and the 6 mm Ball Ended Allen Key supplied, tighten the Camshaft Timing Tensioner ","service tool T3880419"," to 0.6 Nm preset by ","service tool T3880609",".","T3880419 - Camshaft Timing Tensioner","T3880609 - Timing Torque Limiter","6 mm Ball Ended Allen Key","Tighten the two accessible camshaft sprocket fixings to ","22 Nm",".","Fixings","Remove ","service tool T3880421","T3880421 - Camshaft Timing Plate","Camshaft slots","Remove ","service tool T3880422",".","T3880422 - Crankshaft Timing Pin","Timing hole in crankcase","Rotate the engine until the remaining two sprocket fixings are accessible.","Tighten the two remaining camshaft sprocket fixings to ","22 Nm",".","Turn the engine one turn clockwise until the pin can be inserted fully into the crankshaft.","T3880422 - Crankshaft Timing Pin","Timing hole in crankcase","Place a suitable wedge between the camshaft drive chain tensioner blade and crankcase, to hold the camshaft drive chain taut during removal of ","service tool T3880419",". ","Release the tension on ","service tool T3880419"," and remove it.","Refit the camshaft drive chain tensioner, incorporating a new gasket (see ","Camshaft Drive Chain Tensioner - Installation",").","Remove the wedge.","Push the tensioner blade against the tensioner until its retaining clip is released and the tensioner becomes active.","Rotate the crankshaft clockwise two complete turns, using the fixing fitted to the end of the crankshaft. Stop rotation when number 1 cylinder is at top dead centre (TDC).","Insert ","service tool T3880422"," into the timing holes in the crankcase and crankshaft. ","Check that the timing marks are still approximately aligned to check that the camshaft timing is correct.","Remove ","service tool T3880422",".","Refit the spark plugs (see ","Spark Plugs - Renew",").","Perform the following operations:","Camshaft Drive Chain Tensioner - Installation","Crankshaft End Cover - Installation","Camshaft Cover - Installation"],"viewCount":0,"infoType":"InfoType08","createdAt":"2024-04-15T13:50:55.398Z","updatedAt":"2024-04-15T13:50:55.398Z","__v":0}